claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: Figure displaying multiple panels of ELISA-measured antibody titers (log₂ scale) against HA head (H3N2, H1pdm09, B/VIC, B/YAM) and HA stalk (H3 and H1 stalk) and fold-rise ratios at day 0 and 1 month post-vaccination across seven repeat vaccination arms: ccIIV4-ccIIV4, ccIIV4-RIV4, RIV4-ccIIV4, RIV4-RIV4, IIV4-ccIIV4, IIV4-RIV4, and IIV4-IIV4. does not support the claim Note: Brand names for IIV4 and ccIIV4 are not specified, and this figure appears to be from a small repeat-vaccination immunogenicity study rather than the pivotal trial comparing Flublok against Fluarix.
